4301.definition: [προλαμβάνω] from {{G4253}} and {{G2983}}; to take in advance, i.e. (literally) eat before others have an opportunity; (figuratively) to anticipate, surprise

4302.definition: [προλέγω] from {{G4253}} and {{G3004}}; to say beforehand, i.e. predict, forewarn

4303.definition: [προμαρτύρομαι] from {{G4253}} and {{G3143}}; to be a witness in advance i.e. predict

4305.definition: [προμεριμνάω] from {{G4253}} and {{G3309}}; to care (anxiously) in advance

4306.definition: [προνοέω] from {{G4253}} and {{G3539}}; to consider in advance, i.e. look out for beforehand (actively, by way of maintenance for others; middle voice by way of circumspection for oneself)

4307.definition: [πρόνοια] from {{G4306}}; forethought, i.e. provident care or supply

4308.definition: [προοράω] from {{G4253}} and {{G3708}}; to behold in advance, i.e. (actively) to notice (another) previously, or (middle voice) to keep in (one's own) view

4309.definition: [προορίζω] from {{G4253}} and {{G3724}}; to limit in advance, i.e. (figuratively) predetermine

4310.definition: [προπάσχω] from {{G4253}} and {{G3958}}; to undergo hardship previously

4311.definition: [προπέμπω] from {{G4253}} and {{G3992}}; to send forward, i.e. escort or aid in travel

4312.definition: [προπετής] from a compound of {{G4253}} and {{G4098}}; falling forward, i.e. headlong (figuratively, precipitate)

4313.definition: [προπορεύομαι] from {{G4253}} and {{G4198}}; to precede (as guide or herald)

4314.definition: [πρός] a strengthened form of {{G4253}}; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. toward (with the genitive case, the side of, i.e. pertaining to; with the dative case, by the side of, i.e. near to; usually with the accusative case, the place, time, occasion, or respect, which is the destination of the relation, i.e. whither or for which it is predicated) In the comparative case, it denotes essentially the same applications, namely, motion towards, accession to, or nearness at.

4315.definition: [προσάββατον] from {{G4253}} and {{G4521}}; a fore-sabbath, i.e. the Sabbath-eve Compare {{G3904}}.

4316.definition: [προσαγορεύω] from {{G4314}} and a derivative of {{G58}} (mean to harangue); to address, i.e. salute by name

4317.definition: [προσάγω] from {{G4314}} and {{G71}}; to lead towards, i.e. (transitively) to conduct near (summon, present), or (intransitively) to approach

4319.definition: [προσαιτέω] from {{G4314}} and {{G154}}; to ask repeatedly (importune), i.e. solicit

4320.definition: [προσαναβαίνω] from {{G4314}} and {{G305}}; to ascend farther, i.e. be promoted (take an upper (more honorable) seat)

4322.definition: [προσαναπληρόω] from {{G4314}} and {{G378}}; to fill up further, i.e. furnish fully

4323.definition: [προσανατίθημι] from {{G4314}} and {{G394}}; to lay up in addition, i.e. (middle voice and figuratively) to impart or (by implication) to consult

4324.definition: [προσαπειλέω] from {{G4314}} and {{G546}}; to menace additionallye. threaten further.

4326.definition: [προσδέομαι] from {{G4314}} and {{G1189}}; to require additionally, i.e. want further

4327.definition: [προσδέχομαι] from {{G4314}} and {{G1209}}; to admit (to intercourse, hospitality, credence, or (figuratively) endurance); by implication, to await (with confidence or patience)

4328.definition: [προσδοκάω] from {{G4314}} and dokeuo (to watch); to anticipate (in thought, hope or fear); by implication, to await

4329.definition: [προσδοκία] from {{G4328}}; apprehension (of evil); by implication, infliction anticipated

4330.definition: [προσεάω] from {{G4314}} and {{G1439}}; to permit further progress

4332.definition: [προσεδρεύω] from a compound of {{G4314}} and the base of {{G1476}}; to sit near, i.e. attend as a servant

4333.definition: [προσεργάζομαι] from {{G4314}} and {{G2038}}; to work additionally, i.e. (by implication) acquire besides

4334.definition: [προσέρχομαι] from {{G4314}} and {{G2064}} (including its alternate); to approach, i.e. (literally) come near, visit, or (figuratively) worship, assent to

4335.definition: [προσευχή] from {{G4336}}; prayer (worship); by implication, an oratory (chapel)

4336.definition: [προσεύχομαι] from {{G4314}} and {{G2172}}; to pray to God, i.e. supplicate, worship

4337.definition: [προσέχω] from {{G4314}} and {{G2192}}; (figuratively) to hold the mind (3563 implied) towards, i.e. pay attention to, be cautious about, apply oneself to, adhere to

4338.definition: [προσηλόω] from {{G4314}} and a derivative of {{G2247}}; to peg to, i.e. spike fast

4339.definition: [προσήλυτος] from the alternate of {{G4334}}; an arriver from a foreign region, i.e. (specially), an acceder (convert) to Judaism ("proselyte")

4340.definition: [πρόσκαιρος] from {{G4314}} and {{G2540}}; for the occasion only, i.e. temporary

4341.definition: [προσκαλέομαι] middle voice from {{G4314}} and {{G2564}}; to call toward oneself, i.e. summon, invite

4342.definition: [προσκαρτερέω] from {{G4314}} and {{G2594}}; to be earnest towards, i.e. (to a thing) to persevere, be constantly diligent, or (in a place) to attend assiduously all the exercises, or (to a person) to adhere closely to (as a servitor)

4344.definition: [προσκεφάλαιον] neuter of a presumed compound of {{G4314}} and {{G2776}}; something for the head, i.e. a cushion

4345.definition: [προσκληρόω] from {{G4314}} and {{G2820}}; to give a common lot to, i.e. (figuratively) to associate with

4346.definition: [πρόσκλισις] from a compound of {{G4314}} and {{G2827}}; a leaning towards, i.e. (figuratively) proclivity (favoritism)

4347.definition: [προσκολλάω] from {{G4314}} and {{G2853}}; to glue to, i.e. (figuratively) to adhere

4348.definition: [πρόσκομμα] from {{G4350}}; a stub, i.e. (figuratively) occasion of apostasy

4349.definition: [προσκοπή] from {{G4350}}; a stumbling, i.e. (figuratively and concretely) occasion of sin

4350.definition: [προσκόπτω] from {{G4314}} and {{G2875}}; to strike at, i.e. surge against (as water); specially, to stub on, i.e. trip up (literally or figuratively)

4351.definition: [προσκυλίω] from {{G4314}} and {{G2947}}; to roll towards, i.e. block against

4352.definition: [προσκυνέω] from {{G4314}} and a probable derivative of {{G2965}} (meaning to kiss, like a dog licking his master's hand); to fawn or crouch to, i.e. (literally or figuratively) prostrate oneself in homage (do reverence to, adore)

4354.definition: [προσλαλέω] from {{G4314}} and {{G2980}}; to talk to, i.e. converse with

4355.definition: [προσλαμβάνω] from {{G4314}} and {{G2983}}; to take to oneself, i.e. use (food), lead (aside), admit (to friendship or hospitality)

4357.definition: [προσμένω] from {{G4314}} and {{G3306}}; to stay further, i.e. remain in a place, with a person; figuratively, to adhere to, persevere in

4358.definition: [προσορμίζω] from {{G4314}} and a derivative of the same as {{G3730}} (meaning to tie (anchor) or lull); to moor to, i.e. (by implication) land at

4359.definition: [προσοφείλω] from {{G4314}} and {{G3784}}; to be indebted additionally

4360.definition: [προσοχθίζω] from {{G4314}} and a form of ὀχθέω (to be vexed with something irksome); to feel indignant at

4361.definition: [πρόσπεινος] from {{G4314}} and the same as {{G3983}}; hungering further, i.e. intensely hungry

4362.definition: [προσπήγνυμι] from {{G4314}} and {{G4078}}; to fasten to, i.e. (specially), to impale (on a cross)

4363.definition: [προσπίπτω] from {{G4314}} and {{G4098}}; to fall towards, i.e. (gently) prostrate oneself (in supplication or homage), or (violently) to rush upon (in storm)

4364.definition: [προσποιέομαι] middle voice from {{G4314}} and {{G4160}}; to do forward for oneself, i.e. pretend (as if about to do a thing)

4365.definition: [προσπορεύομαι] from {{G4314}} and {{G4198}}; to journey towards, i.e. approach (not the same as {{G4313}})

4366.definition: [προσρήγνυμι] from {{G4314}} and {{G4486}}; to tear towards, i.e. burst upon (as a tempest or flood)

4367.definition: [προστάσσω] from {{G4314}} and {{G5021}}; to arrange towards, i.e. (figuratively) enjoin

4368.definition: [προστάτις] feminine of a derivative of {{G4291}}; a patroness, i.e. assistant

4369.definition: [προστίθημι] from {{G4314}} and {{G5087}}; to place additionally, i.e. lay beside, annex, repeat

4370.definition: [προστρέχω] from {{G4314}} and {{G5143}} (including its alternate); to run towards, i.e. hasten to meet or join

4371.definition: [προσφάγιον] neuter of a presumed derivative of a compound of {{G4314}} and {{G5315}}; something eaten in addition to bread, i.e. a relish (specially, fish; compare {{G3795}})

4372.definition: [πρόσφατος] from {{G4253}} and a derivative of {{G4969}}; previously (recently) slain (fresh), i.e. (figuratively) lately made

4374.definition: [προσφέρω] from {{G4314}} and {{G5342}} (including its alternate); to bear towards, i.e. lead to, tender (especially to God), treat

4375.definition: [προσφιλής] from a presumed compound of {{G4314}} and {{G5368}}; friendly towards, i.e. acceptable

4376.definition: [προσφορά] from {{G4374}}; presentation; concretely, an oblation (bloodless) or sacrifice

4377.definition: [προσφωνέω] from {{G4314}} and {{G5455}}; to sound towards, i.e. address, exclaim, summon

4378.definition: [πρόσχυσις] from a comparative of {{G4314}} and χέω (to pour); a shedding forth, i.e. affusion

4379.definition: [προσψαύω] from {{G4314}} and ψαύω (to touch); to impinge, i.e. lay a finger on (in order to relieve)

4380.definition: [προσωποληπτέω] from {{G4381}}; to favor an individual, i.e. show partiality

4381.definition: [προσωπολήπτης] from {{G4383}} and {{G2983}}; an accepter of a face (individual), i.e. (specially), one exhibiting partiality

4383.definition: [πρόσωπον] from {{G4314}} and ὤψ (the visage, from {{G3700}}); the front (as being towards view), i.e. the countenance, aspect, appearance, surface; by implication, presence, person

4384.definition: [προτάσσω] from {{G4253}} and {{G5021}}; to pre-arrange, i.e. prescribe

4385.definition: [προτείνω] from {{G4253}} and τείνω (to stretch); to protend, i.e. tie prostrate (for scourging)

4386.definition: [πρότερον] neuter of {{G4387}} as adverb (with or without the article); previously

4388.definition: [προτίθεμαι] middle voice from {{G4253}} and {{G5087}}; to place before, i.e. (for oneself) to exhibit; (to oneself) to propose (determine)

4389.definition: [προτρέπομαι] middle voice from {{G4253}} and the base of {{G5157}}; to turn forward for oneself, i.e. encourage

4390.definition: [προτρέχω] from {{G4253}} and {{G5143}} (including its alternate); to run forward, i.e. outstrip, precede

4391.definition: [προϋπάρχω] from {{G4253}} and {{G5225}}; to exist before, i.e. (adverbially) to be or do something previously

4392.definition: [πρόφασις] from a compound of {{G4253}} and {{G5316}}; an outward showing, i.e. pretext

4393.definition: [προφέρω] from {{G4253}} and {{G5342}}; to bear forward, i.e. produce

4395.definition: [προφητεύω] from {{G4396}}; to foretell events, divine, speak under inspiration, exercise the prophetic office

4396.definition: [προφήτης] from a compound of {{G4253}} and {{G5346}}; a foreteller ("prophet"); by analogy, an inspired speaker; by extension, a poet

4398.definition: [προφῆτις] feminine of {{G4396}}; a female foreteller or an inspired woman

4399.definition: [προφθάνω] from {{G4253}} and {{G5348}}; to get an earlier start of, i.e. anticipate

4400.definition: [προχειρίζομαι] middle voice from {{G4253}} and a derivative of {{G5495}}; to handle for oneself in advance, i.e. (figuratively) to purpose
